      </userestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_4a22ca8f16d6e7ed2d51c849c8ba3de6">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Joaquim Sancho, Spanish Nationalist and soldier in the Spanish Civil War, served in the Regular Spanish Army, No. 55, VIII Grupo. In 1939, he was transferred to the 4th Company, 103rd Mixed Brigade. He had three other family members fighting for the Republicans, one in the 141st Mixed Brigade and another in the 109th Mixed Brigade, 3rd Battalion, Major of Transmissions. Following his rehabilitation, he served in the Spanish army in Morocco.</p>  
      </bioghist>
